(44, 21, 16, 57, 1, 9, 9, 'old disciple', 'Connection of Discipleship and Age', 'This connection highlights the theme of discipleship and age, as both passages mention individuals who are described in relation to their experience and maturity. Mnason is referred to as an ''old disciple,'' while Paul identifies himself as ''Paul the aged.''', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 17, 44, 15, 4, 4, 'received us gladly', 'Reception in Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize the positive reception of believers in Jerusalem. In Acts 21:17, the brethren received Paul and his companions gladly, while Acts 15:4 highlights their reception by the church, apostles, and elders.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 17, 45, 15, 7, 7, 'received us', 'Theme of Reception', 'This connection highlights the theme of receiving one another. Both passages emphasize the importance of acceptance within the community of believers.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 17, 58, 13, 1, 2, 'received us gladly', 'Connection of Brotherly Love', 'This connection highlights the theme of hospitality and brotherly love. Both passages emphasize the importance of welcoming others, as seen in the glad reception in Jerusalem and the encouragement to entertain strangers.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 17, 44, 21, 7, 7, 'brethren received us gladly', 'Journey to Jerusalem', 'Both passages emphasize the arrival and reception of Paul and his companions by fellow believers. In Acts 21:7, they greet the brethren in Ptolemais, while in Acts 21:17, they are received gladly in Jerusalem, highlighting a continuity of fellowship.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 17, 64, 1, 7, 8, 'received us gladly', 'Reception of Believers', 'This connection highlights the theme of receiving fellow believers. Both passages emphasize the importance of welcoming those who serve for the sake of the truth.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 18, 48, 1, 19, 19, 'James', 'Connection Between Paul and James', 'This connection highlights the presence of James in both passages. In Acts, Paul meets with James, while in Galatians, Paul mentions seeing James specifically.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 18, 44, 11, 30, 30, 'elders', 'Connection through Elders', 'Both passages emphasize the role of elders in the early church. In Acts 21:18, Paul meets with James and the elders, while Acts 11:30 mentions sending aid to the elders.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 18, 44, 15, 13, 13, 'James', 'Connection through James'' Leadership', 'Both passages emphasize the role of James in the early church. In Acts 21:18, Paul meets with James, indicating his leadership, while Acts 15:13 shows James addressing the assembly, highlighting his authority.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 18, 48, 2, 9, 9, 'James', 'Connection Between Paul and James', 'This connection highlights the relationship between Paul and James, as both passages mention James in significant roles. Acts 21:18 introduces James as a leader present with the elders, while Galatians 2:9 shows him as a key figure in recognizing Paul''s mission.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 18, 40, 10, 2, 2, 'James; and all the elders were present', 'Connection Between Paul and James', 'This connection highlights the presence of James in both passages. In Acts, Paul meets with James, while in Matthew, James is named among the apostles, indicating his significance in the early church.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 18, 59, 1, 1, 1, 'James; and all the elders were present', 'Connection Between Paul and James', 'This connection highlights the presence of James and the elders in Acts, linking them to the greeting in James 1:1. Both passages emphasize the role of James in the early church and his connection to the scattered tribes.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 19, 44, 14, 27, 27, 'what things God had wrought', 'God''s Work Among the Gentiles', 'Both passages emphasize what God has done among the Gentiles. Acts 21:19 mentions ''what things God had wrought'' while Acts 14:27 refers to ''how he had opened the door of faith unto the Gentiles.''', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 19, 44, 1, 17, 17, NULL, 'Connection of Ministry and Service', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of ministry, with Acts 21:19 highlighting the work done among the Gentiles and Acts 1:17 referencing the inclusion in this ministry. This connection highlights the continuity of service in the early church.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 19, 45, 15, 18, 19, 'what things God had wrought among the Gentiles', 'Connection of Gentile Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the work among the Gentiles, highlighting the results of Paul''s ministry. Acts 21:19 mentions what God accomplished through him, while Romans 15:18-19 details how he made the Gentiles obedient through signs and wonders.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 19, 46, 15, 10, 10, 'what things God had wrought', 'Connection of Grace and Labor', 'Both passages emphasize the role of God''s grace in the ministry of Paul. Acts 21:19 highlights what God accomplished through him, while 1 Corinthians 15:10 reflects on his labor being empowered by that same grace.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 19, 46, 3, 5, 9, 'what things God had wrought among the Gentiles', 'Ministry and Growth Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of ministers in spreading the faith and highlight that it is ultimately God who brings about growth and results. Acts 21:19 mentions the work done among the Gentiles, while 1 Corinthians 3:5-9 discusses the collaborative efforts of Paul and Apollos in ministry.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 19, 47, 6, 1, 1, 'what things God had wrought among the Gentiles', 'Connection of Ministry and Grace', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s work among the Gentiles and the call to not receive His grace in vain. Both passages emphasize the importance of recognizing and responding to God''s actions in ministry.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 19, 47, 12, 12, 12, 'what things God had wrought', 'Signs of Apostolic Ministry', 'Both passages emphasize the miraculous works attributed to apostolic ministry. Acts 21:19 mentions what God wrought among the Gentiles, while 2 Corinthians 12:12 refers to signs and wonders done among the Corinthians.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 20, 45, 10, 2, 2, 'zealous of the law', 'Zeal for the Law', 'This connection highlights the theme of zeal present in both passages. Acts 21:20 mentions Jews who are ''zealous of the law,'' while Romans 10:2 speaks of a ''zeal of God,'' indicating a shared fervor that may lack proper understanding.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 20, 48, 1, 14, 14, 'zealous of the law', 'Zeal for the Law and Traditions', 'This connection highlights the shared theme of zeal for religious practices. Both passages emphasize being ''zealous of the law'' and ''zealous of the traditions of my fathers,'' indicating a strong commitment to Jewish religious customs.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 20, 44, 22, 3, 3, 'zealous of the law', 'Zealousness for the Law', 'Both passages emphasize zeal for the law. In Acts 21:20, the believers are described as ''zealous of the law,'' while in Acts 22:3, Paul identifies himself as ''zealous toward God,'' linking their fervor for the law and God.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 20, 44, 11, 18, 18, NULL, 'Glorifying God for Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the act of glorifying God in response to the spread of faith among different groups. In Acts 21:20, the believers glorify the Lord for the Jewish believers'' zeal, while in Acts 11:18, they glorify God for granting repentance to the Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 20, 19, 22, 23, 23, 'glorified the Lord', 'Praise and Glorification of God', 'This connection highlights the theme of glorifying the Lord found in both passages. Acts 21:20 mentions believers glorifying the Lord, while Psalms 22:23 calls on the seed of Jacob to glorify Him.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 20, 19, 72, 17, 19, NULL, 'Connection of Blessing and Zeal', 'This connection highlights the theme of blessing and zeal for God. Both passages emphasize the enduring nature of God''s name and the fervent devotion of His followers.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 20, 23, 55, 10, 13, 'zealous of the law', 'Connection of Zeal and Accomplishment', 'Both passages emphasize the fulfillment of God''s purpose. In Acts, the zeal of Jewish believers reflects a commitment to God''s law, while Isaiah speaks of God''s word accomplishing its intended purpose. This connection highlights the active role of faith in realizing divine promises.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 21, 46, 9, 19, 21, 'forsake Moses', 'Paul''s Adaptability to Cultures', 'This connection highlights Paul''s approach to ministry, where he adapts to different cultural contexts. In Acts, he is accused of teaching Jews to forsake Moses, while in Corinthians, he emphasizes becoming like a Jew to gain them.', 'theme', 0.349, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 21, 48, 6, 12, 15, 'to forsake Moses', 'Circumcision and the Law', 'Both passages emphasize the issue of circumcision and its relation to the law. Acts 21:21 mentions teaching against circumcision, while Galatians 6:12-15 discusses the pressure to be circumcised and the futility of such practices in Christ.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 21, 48, 5, 1, 6, 'circumcise their children', 'Connection on Circumcision and Law', 'Both passages emphasize the implications of circumcision and adherence to the law. Acts 21:21 mentions teaching against circumcision, while Galatians 5:2-3 warns that being circumcised obligates one to the whole law, suggesting a shared theme of freedom from legalistic practices.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 21, 21, 44, 15, 19, 21, 'forsake Moses', 'Connection Between Jewish Customs and Gentiles', 'This connection highlights the tension between Jewish customs and the inclusion of Gentiles in the faith. Both passages address the issue of adherence to Moses and the customs, emphasizing the need for Gentiles to abstain from certain practices while acknowledging the ongoing presence of Moses in synagogues.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
